				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$2.5 \times 10^6 \,\mathrm{K}$$\end{document}. Although these models are highly simplified, the use of the lithium abundance as a constraint on the extent of convective mixing, and the effect of a composition adjustment on the convection-zone depth, remain highly relevant, as discussed below.

