The thermodynamic properties of stellar matter, defined by the equation of state, play a crucial role in stellar modelling. This directly involves the relation between pressure, density, temperature and composition. In addition, the adiabatic compressibility Γ1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
