				\begin{document}$$2 \times 10^6 \,\mathrm{K}$$\end{document}. This followed an earlier plea by Simon (1982) for a reexamination of the opacity calculations in connection with problems in the interpretation of double-mode Cepheids and in the understanding of the excitation of oscillations in β\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
