				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$s_{\mathrm{conv}}$$\end{document}; in other words, the variations of the thermodynamical quantities within this part of the convection zone lie on an adiabat. In fact, if the further approximation of a fully ionized ideal gas is made, such as is roughly valid except in the outer few per cent of the solar radius, ∇ad≃2/5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
