The later evolution of stars of solar mass is discussed in detail by Kippenhahn et al. (2012). The specific case of the Sun was considered by, for example, Jørgensen (1991) and Sackmann et al. (1993). With continuing core contraction and expansion of the envelope the star moves up along the Hayashi track as a red giant, reaching a luminosity of more than 2000L⊙\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
