				\begin{document}$$l = 0$$\end{document}), between observed and modelled solar oscillation frequencies against frequency, in the sense (Sun)–(Model). The dot-dashed curve uses adiabatic frequencies for a model essentially corresponding to Model S (Christensen-Dalsgaard et al. 1996, see Sect. 4.1). The solid curve is based on a model where the outermost layers were replaced by a suitable average of a three-dimensional radiative-hydrodynamic simulation of convection. In addition, the frequencies were obtained from nonadiabatic calculations taking the interaction with convection, including turbulent pressure, into account. 
