The original discrepancy between the neutrino measurements and the model predictions immediately led to attempts to modify solar models so as to reduce the neutrino flux. In most cases, this was done under the constraint that the total solar nuclear energy generation rate was kept unchanged. The initial detection with the 37Cl\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
