				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${{}^{8}\mathrm{B}}$$\end{document} reactions. Thus the predicted capture rate depended strongly on the branching ratios between the PP-II and PP-I, and the PP-III and PP-II, chains (cf. Eqs. 24, 25), which in turn are very sensitive to temperature; at fixed nuclear luminosity the flux of 8B\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
