				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${{}^{3}\mathrm{He}}$$\end{document} through the second reaction in the PP-I chain (cf. Eq. 24) which takes place at temperatures as low as those found in the present solar convection zone. From estimates of the primordial solar-system content of 2D\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
