				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\bar{\rho }}$$\end{document} is the mean density of the star. In particular, for solar-like oscillations, i.e., acoustic modes of high radial order, the large frequency separation (cf. Eq. 59) satisfies Δν∝ρ¯1/2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
